About Rockland Luggage Since its inception in 1998, Rockland by Fox Luggage has been proudly producing quality luggage and bags for the style savvy traveler. Recognized for its graphic and colorful designs, Rockland prides itself on creating products influenced by current trends in design and fashion. Our products turn heads in a crowd and stand out in the baggage carousel, making it easy for quick exits out the airport. Affordable and travel resistant, Rockland bags are an ideal companion for everything from quick trips to the gym to overnight getaways to extended vacations. Our selection includes: luggage sets (4 piece, 3 piece or 2 piece), hard cases, soft cases, carry ons, rolling backpacks, travel duffels, rolling duffels, cosmetic bags, and kids' backpacks. Over the years, a few Rockland products have been featured in film and television. Their colorful designs make them ideal for an eye catching visual element on screen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 21, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I desperately needed a new suitcase, and wanted one that rolled easily, was lighter than my old suitcase, and extremely sturdy. This one was exactly what I wanted. It’s significantly lighter than my old suitcase, which means, even when packed, I can lift it into the car or off the airline luggage return without strain.The zippers work smoothly, although I was a bit concerned when I first saw the new suitcase. The zippers seemed too small for the job they have…BUT after the first 2 trips I became convinced they were much better and certainly strong enough to do the job.I also like the clamshell style-easy to pack and organize, with personal items on one side and clothing on the other.The suitcase survived the typical airline abuse without a scratch or dent; and makes weekend and long trips effortless because I can get everything in it. Best of all it has an expandable feature that I didn’t expect. I haven’t needed it yet, but it’s nice to know it’s there if necessary.I’m glad I bought this bag-it’s well worth the price (which was lower than my second choice!)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect Travel suitcase!
reviews.reviewText: I got these recently for a trip abroad and these were PERFECT! There was plenty of space for all my things, I loved how easy they were to move through the airports. And I loved that my things were SAFE! The ability to lock both bags made me feel much more comfortable, and the fact that the hard case protected everything inside was even better.Traveling is stressful enough as it is, I'm glad I didn't have to worry even more about my belongings.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars More modern transport for me!
reviews.reviewText: Got rid of my old Samsonite and got this pair. The wheels spin in a 360 degree circle, which makes it easier to pull. Used it to visit my sis in Chicago. Good color, great price!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Traveled out the country with this set. Durable so far, but nervous about how long it will last.
reviews.reviewText: My luggage came is two days as projected. Seemed a bit frail, but it's held up for the most part so far.Pros- Nice in color. Seemed fragile as I packed 50lbs of clothes/shoes in the 28inch case, but it is still in good shape and managed to serve it's purpose. Very spacious set. The expandable zipper is a bonus. Plastic separators with a zipper were a huge convenience. Shoes on one side clothes on another for both sets.Cons- The luggage lock is extremely cheap and broke upon my destination arrival on the 28inch case. The smell of the luggage is not the most appeasing, but it is new. (should've "frebreezed" it before I packed, not fond of the plastic smell lingering on my clothes). After I landed I noticed strings hanging from the outside lining by where the zipper tracks are. I cute them off when I arrived, but after I departed from the trip and picked my bags up from baggage claim and noticed a few more strings hanging. I would be lying if i said I'm not worried about the longevity of this set.I would recommend this set to others, but be aware you get what you pay for. I in-vision me using the 20inch piece more than the 28inch piece. Not sure how long they both will last though.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: A good value. Held up nicely for overseas trip

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars One of the wheels on the 28" suitcase ripped off the very first time I used it.
reviews.reviewText: I was given the smaller size ( in orange) and liked it so much I gave it to a friend and ordered another small AND a big size in grey. I was thrilled with the look and the space.However, the very first time I went travelling with the larger one, one of the rolling wheels literally ripped off with a big chunk of plastic ( not the screws). I was not carrying it by the wheel or dragging it; I literally reached out to spin it and it broke. It cannot be screwed back on or glued. It is unusable as a 4-wheeled suitcase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great value for a great price!
reviews.reviewText: 4 Flights and numerous road trips later, the suitcases hold up perfectly. The wheels work great, suit case is roomy and the zippers are sturdy. The extended handles are a bit flimsy. Color is a true champagne.Would buy them again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 27, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Love the color! Beautiful Set. Rolls smoothly. Light but sturdy. Both expand. 20” fits perfectly in the 28”. I hope to figure out a way to set the smaller one on top and secure it so I only have to pull one into the airport.
Las maletas se sienten muy bien, ligeras, rígidas, los cierres funcionan bien, las ruedas giran y se desplazan rápidamente, incluye un candado de combinación cada maleta.
Looks good, light. Hope it's durable as haven't taken to a trip

Aunque aún no las he utilizado, se ven de buena calidad, sobre todo las ruedas se notan robustas. Vienen forradas de tela por el interior, una tela gris con estampado de dibujo blanco, bonito. Esta tela es normalita, pero suficiente. La maleta grande es generosa en tamaño, la pequeña esta muy bien para por ejemplo meter los zapatos. Traen su correspondiente candado cada una, ya sabemos que son candados muy simples, por lo que si quieres mas seguridad puedes comprar uno de los buenos, aunque si quieren abrir la maleta la abren de todos modos... esta y cualquiera.En general, muy contento con la compra, una calidad mas que aceptable solo queda ver si mis impresiones son acertadas con el uso y el tiempo. Recomiendo la compra.Como añadido decir, que solo pude escoger las grises con tonos naranjas, y la verdad es que son muy bonitas y elegantes, en las fotos se ven bien, pero en la realidad se ven de otra manera. Muy bonitas.

reviews.reviewTitle: Great colour, easy to identify, just ok for the price!
reviews.reviewText: I’ve been on several long haul trips with them so far. I really like the fashionable aesthetics of the suitcase set, the colours makes it very easy to see when it’s coming off the carousel at the airport.I don’t like the inside so much I feel the quality is lacking. The inside zipper that separates each side broke on my first trip, so all my clothes fall to the other side when I open it. Also the separation doesn’t have any storage compartments which would have been a nice feature especially in the carry on size. Make sure to fill the corners of the case when flighting as one of the corners on the large case sunk in from air pressure. The locks that were included were cheap so I add my own.They are very easy to manoeuvre and a good price for a set compared to many of the stores.

reviews.reviewText: So far I haven't used them yet, but they are pretty! I'm a bit nervous because the case is not very hard and protective. We will have to see in action. The wheels are very easy to move around, and the zippers seem sturdy. It is definitely very light which is great.
